snippet.textDisplay: Great line up Coke Studio but I really think the sound and the mix of all the instruments together with vocals doesnt gel well together. Its a production issue I believe. Hardly any other instruments are audible except dholak and the claps. I hope if Hamza and co continue again in future they really work out the mix better. Considering this is their first time I guess there is still learning. Same was with Ghoom Charkhara. The artists are amazing and I think they should be supported with proper sound. I heard Hamza's song Hor Vi Neevan and hear how each and every instrument is crystal clear. That is just my constructive criticism for something that is a Pride of Pakistan Coke Studio. Best Wishes and God Bless you guys!
snippet.textOriginal: Great line up Coke Studio but I really think the sound and the mix of all the instruments together with vocals doesnt gel well together. Its a production issue I believe. Hardly any other instruments are audible except dholak and the claps. I hope if Hamza and co continue again in future they really work out the mix better. Considering this is their first time I guess there is still learning. Same was with Ghoom Charkhara. The artists are amazing and I think they should be supported with proper sound.
